<title>TURKEY: Istanbul gold volume falls amid price volatility.</title>
<headline>Istanbul gold volume falls amid price volatility.</headline>
<dateline>ISTANBUL 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Volume on the Istanbul gold exchange shrank on Friday as traders took to the sidelines because of volatility in international gold markets, dealers said.</p>
<p>Total turnover of 205 kilos was in lira terms, with 195 kilos traded in the afternoon.</p>
<p>Volume was 360 kilos on Thursday.</p>
<p>Gold closed at 1,236,000 lira per gram, up from Thursday's 1,231,800 lira, reflecting the trend in Europe.</p>
<p>-- Istanbul newsroom +90-212-275 08 75</p>
